Class EmployeeSet

java.lang.Object
Employee.EmployeeSet
public class EmployeeSet extends Object

    • add

      public void add​(Employee.Employee e)
      Add a new Employee object to the collection,
      Parameters:
      e - The Employee to add to the collection.
      precondition
      The employee object should NOT be null.
      postcondition
      If the employee is a duplicate, no change will be made, if the Employee object is not null, the Employee will be added to the next available spot in the collection.

    • remove

      public boolean remove​(int eno)
      Remove an Employee object from the collection via their employee number.
      Parameters:
      eno - Employee number.
      Returns:
      True if employee was successfully removed | False if no employee found.
      postcondition
      If employee was found in collection, returns true if it was removed, else, return false, as no employee was found with the given employee number.

    • contains

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      True if Employee is in the set. | False if Employee is not found.
